        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "He wrote that “some plans may violate the Affordable Care Act’s (ACA) patient protections by making an initial coverage determination based on final diagnosis codes and then applying the prudent layperson standard only if the participant, beneficiary, or enrollee appeals or seeks further consideration of the claim. Other plans or issuers may inappropriately require ‘sudden onset’ of the emergency medical condition or impose a time limit between the onset of symptoms and the patient’s presentation at the emergency department.”",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
