            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "“These activities,” Kahn wrote, “impose inappropriate burdens on patients receiving and providers or facilities furnishing both in-network and out-of-network services, and, in the context of emergency services, generate surprise bills, cause patients to forego seeking emergency services, and burden emergency facilities and providers with unnecessary disputes and administrative burdens.”",
